cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses learning from data and the effectiveness and efficiency of cooperative inference. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with agents and their goals. The paper's focus on analyzing consistency, rate of convergence, and stability suggests it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The discussion of human-human and human-machine cooperation suggests it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper's use of Bayesian inference suggests it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
